<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 01 at 2:56PM EDT  by NWS Columbia</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Burke
County through 330 PM EDT...
At 256 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Perkins, or 9 miles northwest of Millen, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Sardis, Midville, Alexander, Girard, Vidette, Di-
Lane Wildlife Management Area, Magruder and Rosier.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
